## 4. Core Architecture — Agreed & Final

### 4.1 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Why / Notes |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| **App Framework** | React Native + Expo SDK 52+ | Single codebase: Android + iOS + Web. TypeScript throughout. Best AI coding support. |
| **Web Support** | React Native Web (via Expo) | Web gets full feature parity. No separate codebase. Same screens, same RE, same backend. |
| **Navigation** | Expo Router (file-based) | Matches IA screen structure exactly. Deep linking for notifications. Works on web too. |
| **State** | Zustand + React Query | Zustand = lightweight in-memory. React Query = server cache + offline + background refresh. |
| **Gestures** | Gesture Handler + Reanimated 3 | Native 60fps swipe/long-press. Non-negotiable for the core swipe UX. |
| **Backend** | Supabase | PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Edge Functions + Realtime. Free tier: 500MB DB, 50K MAU. |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (inside Supabase) | Full SQL for RE scoring queries, joins, aggregations, full-text search. |
| **Server Functions** | Supabase Edge Functions (Deno/TypeScript) | RE scoring, plan generation, weather fetch, analytics aggregation, daily batch. |
| **Auth** | Supabase Auth | Email+password MVP. Google Sign-In Phase 0.5. |
| **Push Notifications** | Expo Notifications + OneSignal | Free: unlimited devices. Morning plan notification at MVP. |
| **Images** | Supabase Storage + Cloudinary CDN | On-the-fly resize, WebP conversion, Blurhash for lazy loading. Free: 25GB bandwidth. |
| **Weather** | OpenWeatherMap API | Free: 1,000 calls/day. City from device GPS or home state capital as fallback. |
| **Analytics** | PostHog | Free: 1M events/month. Tracks every user action from Day 1. |
| **Error Tracking** | Sentry | Free: 5K events/month. Catches crashes before users report them. |
| **CI/CD & Builds** | Expo EAS Build | Cloud builds — no local Xcode or Android Studio needed. OTA updates. |
| **IDE** | GitHub Codespace | Cloud-based IDE. No local machine needed. Fully browser-based coding. |
| **AI Builder** | Claude Code (primary) | Connected to GitHub Codespace. Writes ~70% of code from plain English instructions. |
| **Code Reviewer** | Cursor free tier | For reviewing what Claude Code built, small targeted edits, understanding structure. |

### 4.2 Database: 42 MVP-Active Tables (Doc 11A — FINAL)

Organised into 5 groups:

**Food Knowledge Base (14 tables):** cuisines, dishes (with 20 Food DNA columns), tags, dish_tags, dish_similar, dish_combos, dish_combo_items, ingredients, ingredient_aliases, meal_ingredients, term_synonyms, recipes (empty at MVP), recipe_steps (empty), media_assets

**User & Preferences (11 tables):** profiles, user_diet_rules, user_category_preferences, user_consent, user_feedback, user_inferred_prefs, user_dish_patterns, user_behavioral_profile, family_members, user_recipe_affinity, never_list

**Planner & RE (12 tables + 1 materialized view):** planner, planner_carousel, suggestion_logs, recommendation_debug_log (5% sample), weather_cache, region_food_affinity, experiments, experiment_assignments, daily_plans, dish_popularity (MV — refreshed daily)

**App Intelligence (4 tables):** app_events, user_behavioral_profile (aggregated weekly), experiments, experiment_assignments

**Operations (12 tables):** audit_log, role_audit, etl_jobs, cache_metadata, mv_refresh_history, migration_log, notification_log, referrals (Phase 1), pii_tokens (Phase 1.5+)

**Key architectural choices:**
- Integer IDs for diet exclusions (`excluded_ingredients integer[]`) — no language-matching issues
- `dish_tags` junction for Food DNA — unlimited dimensions post-launch without schema changes
- Polymorphic planner — supports both dishes and combos in same slots
- Decay-weighted history: 7d=1.0, 8–30d=0.5, 31–90d=0.2, 90d+=0.05 (tunable via `decay_config jsonb`)
- All timestamps UTC — IST conversion at Edge Function and client layer only
- Auto-derivation: allergens, diet_type, is_jain computed from ingredient flags, not manual tagging

### 4.3 Recommendation Engine — The Heart of FooFoo

| Version | When | What's Added |
|---------|------|-------------|
| **RE v1** | MVP launch | Hard filters (auto-derived) + onboarding boosts + weather + day-of-week + home state + variety guard + random factor. Combo-aware. |
| **RE v2** | MVP Week 3+ | Personal history scoring + decay curves + inferred spice/texture/complexity + per-user repeat tolerance + cuisine drift. |
| **RE v2.5** | Weeks 4–8 post-launch | Tier 2 Food DNA tags active (cooking_method, texture, richness, heaviness, weather_affinity). +15% acceptance lift expected. |
| **RE v3** | Phase 1.5 (5K+ MAU) | K-means clustering on food DNA similarity. Cluster-seeded new user recommendations. Context tags. |
| **RE v4** | Phase 2–3 | 70% personal + 30% cluster. Mood/mode awareness. Calorie targeting. Tier 3 tags. Pantry-aware. |

**Food DNA Taxonomy (20 Dimensions):**
- **Tier 1 (MVP, 7 dims):** cuisine · diet_type · allergens · spice_level · cook_time_mins · difficulty · calories
- **Tier 2 (Weeks 4–8, 7 dims):** cooking_method · primary_taste · texture · heaviness · richness · sweetness · weather_affinity
- **Tier 3 (Phase 2+, 6 dims):** mouthfeel · aroma_profile · fermentation · serving_temp · health_tags · ingredient_complexity

**RE Sprint 3 fallback plan:** If the full 10-step pipeline is not working by Day 3 of Week 6, switch to simplified: hard filters + cuisine boost + random. Pre-agreed so there is no debate on the day.

### 4.4 Content Model: 3 Levels

| Level | Content | Status at MVP Launch |
