## 11. Code Standards & Documentation Protocol

Every file and function written for FooFoo must follow these standards — applied consistently by Claude and reviewed by founders.

### 11.1 Project Structure
```
foofoo/
├── CLAUDE.md                    ← Context file for Claude Code (read every session)
├── CHANGELOG.md                 ← Master change log
├── src/
│   ├── config/
│   │   └── constants.ts         ← APP_NAME, API URLs, all configurable values here
│   ├── modules/
│   │   ├── recommendation-engine/
│   │   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── home/
│   │   ├── dish-detail/
│   │   ├── search/
│   │   ├── grocery/
│   │   ├── profile/
│   │   └── notifications/
│   ├── services/                ← All API calls go here (never in components)
│   ├── repositories/            ← All Supabase queries go here (never raw SQL in components)
│   ├── components/              ← Shared UI components
│   └── types/                   ← TypeScript type definitions
├── supabase/
│   ├── functions/               ← Edge Functions (RE scoring, plan generation, weather)
│   └── migrations/              ← All schema migrations in sequence
└── app/                         ← Expo Router screens (file = screen)
```

**Rules:**
- No file longer than 300 lines — split into sub-files
- App name: `export const APP_NAME = "Foofoo"` in `constants.ts` — one change, applies everywhere
- All API calls go through `src/services/` — never directly in components
- All Supabase queries go through `src/repositories/` — never raw SQL in screen files
- Every async function wrapped in try/catch; errors logged to Sentry
- Structured logs with `[MODULE_NAME]` prefix: e.g., `[RE-SCORING] Plan generated in 1.2s for user abc123`

